[[Image:Rob_Lucas.jpg|frame|right|Hon. Rob Lucas]]
'''Rob Lucas''' is an [[Australia]]n politician and the [[Liberal Party of Australia]] Leader of the Opposition in the [[South Australian Legislative Council]], and was re-elected in the [[South Australian legislative election, 2006|2006 election]].

Before his entry in to politics, Lucas gained [[Bachelor of Science]] and [[Bachelor of Economics]] degrees, as well as an [[MBA]]. 

In office, Lucas has been a Minister for Education and Children's Services, Minister for Industry and Trade, Minister for Government Enterprises, as well as Treasurer until the [[Liberal Party of Australia|Liberal Party]] defeat in the [[South Australian legislative election, 2002|2002 election]].

